"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-lifestyle-celeb-news-local-celebs-paris-olympics-2024-who-is-south-african-swimmer-tatjana-smith-shoenmaker-rachel-siya-kolisi\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbLifestyle\\u00bbCeleb News\\u00bbLocal Celebs\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024: Who is SA's swimmer Tatjana Smith?  Five things to know about Rachel Kolisi's sister-in-law, Tatjana Smith, who will represent South Africa at the Paris Olympics 2024.  South African swimmerTatjana Smith, formerly Shoenmaker,will be representing the country at the Paris Olympics 2024.  Here are five things to know about one of the country's best chances of a medal.  SASCOC announced\\u00a0the first batch of athletes who will be representing South Africa at the Paris Olympics 2024.  And among many other big names is swimmer Tatjana Smith - formerly Shoenmaker.  Tatjana will be competing in the women's 100m and 200m breaststroke events.  She will be joined by four other South African female swimmers, namely Aimee Canny (200m freestyle), Kaylene Corbett (200m breaststroke), Erin Gallagher (100m butterfly), Rebecca Meder (200m IM).  Meanwhile, there were three male swimmers selected: Pieter Coetze (100m and 200m breaststroke), Chad le Cos (100m butterfly) and Matthew Sates (100m, 200m butterfly and 200m IM).  Tatjana took to Instagram to express her excitement to be competing at the Paris Olympics 2024.  \\\"Annnnd it is OFFICIAL!!!! Paris Olympics 2024 \\ud83c\\uddeb\\ud83c\\uddf7\\ud83d\\uddfc. Congratulations to all the other athletes including my fellow swimmers for making the team . VERY VERY EXCITED to swim for the Glory of God and to represent my country while doing it \\ud83d\\ude4f\\ud83c\\udffc,\\\" she wrote.  A post shared by -TATJANA-SCHOENMAKER- (@tatjanaschoen)  The Paris Olympics 2024 kick off on 26 July and end on 11 August.  The opening ceremony will take place in Jardins du Trocad\\u00e9ro\\u00a0and the\\u00a0Seine, while the closing ceremony will take place at Stade de France.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"